	   <tr><td colspan=2>Awesome work. It seems you have addressed several issues. A few observations/questions fro you:<br>1st the unusual placement of the monk in the class list at 12. <br>2) Concerning exp at hell levels. From you calculations it is apparent there is additional exp needed at 30 (about 30% more) due to increase in level multipler. But it also seems your saying this same multiplier 1.1 is used for levels 31-34. I have felt that it was easier after the hell levels (required less exp) than during one. Also I believe this is so because the amount of exp loss due to a death is more noticeable after a hell level than when in a hell level. This would make sense 1) if a hell level requires more exp so when you die there is less of a visible effect on your level bar. 2) exp loss is based upon a formula similar to the experience formula above.<br>I also believe Verant recently has stated (not a fact here just something I read) that when grp w/hybrids that the exp will be divided such that all group members if the same level just differnet classes will level together. If that is true then in a grp exp isnt divided evenly. Any thoughts?<br>Thanks enjoyed your write up.<br>Robin<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
