	   <tr><td colspan=2>Group xp is split up based on the amount of xp a character currently has (as well as race/clas).<br><br>I have a spreadsheet which was developed a long time ago (pre-kunark) that shows percentages and hard numbers of what is needed to level.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>This spreadsheet and many others XP "spoilers" (including the content for the original thread) have been derived from programs like ShowEQ...or at least that was the claim of the original poster some 8 months ago.<br><br>You will find that a group that wishes to level together needs to have hybrids 1-2 levels higher than group average and halflings or warriors 1-2 lower.  Its a bit complicated to explain without the actual spreadsheet available.  Also I can not remember where I found the spreadsheet...might have been on EverquestHQ, maximumEQ, or even the old stomp.com site...<br><br>Anyway...once you see the charting and the way xp works, it becomes easier to identify where a character needs to be to avoid the worst penalties and get the most reward...<br><br>Thanks for posting this thread.  It is important that this information is shared every few months so that everyone can understand the nature of the beast...  :) <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
